WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:04.137
[***]

00:04.170 --> 00:05.739
NARRATOR:
<i>1982.</i>

00:05.772 --> 00:07.741
<i>That was the year I turned 13.</i>

00:07.774 --> 00:10.477
<i>Before I was a comedian,</i>
<i>I thought the coolest thing</i>

00:10.510 --> 00:14.547
<i>that would happen to me</i>
<i>was being a teenager.</i>

00:14.581 --> 00:19.252
<i>I was going to have women,</i>
<i>money, stay out late...</i>

00:19.285 --> 00:23.423
<i>I thought it was going</i>
<i>to be the bomb.</i>

00:23.456 --> 00:24.724
'Sup?

00:24.758 --> 00:27.160
He's here!
Chris is here!

00:27.193 --> 00:28.361
Yo, Chris!

00:28.395 --> 00:30.296
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

00:30.330 --> 00:32.432
[CHANTING]
<i>Chris! Chris! Chris! Chris!</i>

00:32.465 --> 00:34.567
<i>Chris! Chris! Chris! Chris!</i>

00:34.601 --> 00:36.569
[CHANTING CONTINUES]

00:36.603 --> 00:38.605
NARRATOR:
<i>Boy, was I wrong.</i>

00:38.638 --> 00:40.240
Chris!

00:40.273 --> 00:43.276
Get in the bathroom and wipe
the pee off the toilet seat!

00:44.811 --> 00:46.646
Disgusting!

00:48.682 --> 00:50.617
[***]

00:56.489 --> 01:00.093
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>

01:24.584 --> 01:27.687
JULIUS:
Come on, y'all, let's go.
We got to move.

01:27.721 --> 01:30.924
NARRATOR:
<i>When I was 13,</i>
<i>my mother convinced my father</i>

01:30.957 --> 01:32.459
<i>to move us out</i>
<i>of the projects.</i>

01:32.492 --> 01:33.860
<i>She always said, "'Project'</i>

01:33.893 --> 01:36.663
<i>"is just another word</i>
<i>for 'experiment.'"</i>

01:36.696 --> 01:39.466
<i>In a lab, the government</i>
<i>gives rats cheese.</i>

01:39.499 --> 01:42.669
<i>In the projects, the government</i>
<i>gives people cheese.</i>

01:42.702 --> 01:44.671
Dad...

01:44.704 --> 01:46.306
can we stop at McDonald's?

01:46.339 --> 01:47.874
You got some
McDonald's money?

01:47.907 --> 01:49.342
Julius, the kids
have to eat.

01:49.376 --> 01:50.744
They ain't got
to eat McDonald's.

01:50.777 --> 01:53.213
We got some bologna in the back.
I'll pull over.

01:53.246 --> 01:55.915
NARRATOR:
<i>My father Julius always kept</i>
<i>bologna handy just in case.</i>

01:55.949 --> 01:57.617
We get one combo meal.

01:57.650 --> 01:59.853
Drew gets the burger.
Tanya gets the fries.

01:59.886 --> 02:01.354
Chris, you can
have the drink.

02:01.388 --> 02:03.623
NARRATOR:
<i>One time, I just got ice.</i>

02:03.656 --> 02:05.392
[***]

02:05.425 --> 02:08.628
NARRATOR:
<i>We moved to an apartment</i>
<i>in Bed-Stuy Brooklyn.</i>

02:08.661 --> 02:10.497
<i>Now, had we known</i>
<i>that Bed-Stuy</i>

02:10.530 --> 02:12.665
<i>would be the center</i>
<i>of a crack epidemic,</i>

02:12.699 --> 02:16.236
<i>I guess we would've picked</i>
<i>someplace else.</i>

02:16.269 --> 02:17.904
<i>Bed-Stuy even had</i>
<i>its own motto:</i>

02:17.937 --> 02:20.407
<i>"Bed-Stuy, do or die."</i>

02:20.440 --> 02:22.809
Look at that.
Look at that, look at that.

02:22.842 --> 02:25.378
NARRATOR:
<i>Those are some of the guys</i>
<i>that are going to die.</i>

02:25.412 --> 02:27.514
If I ever catch
any of y'all

02:27.547 --> 02:29.449
spray-painting
on anybody's wall,

02:29.482 --> 02:31.451
I'mma put my foot
so far up your behind,

02:31.484 --> 02:33.853
you'll have toes for teeth.

02:33.887 --> 02:35.388
Get inside.

02:35.422 --> 02:36.856
NARRATOR:
<i>That's my mother Rochelle.</i>

02:36.890 --> 02:39.292
<i>She had a hundred recipes</i>
<i>for whooping ass.</i>

02:39.325 --> 02:41.961
Boy, I will slap the caps
off your knees.

02:41.995 --> 02:44.531
I will knock you
into last night.

02:44.564 --> 02:46.700
I will slap your name
out the phone book

02:46.733 --> 02:48.768
and call Ma Bell
and tell her I did it!

02:48.802 --> 02:50.770
NARRATOR:
<i>That's my younger brother Drew.</i>

02:50.804 --> 02:53.406
<i>There's nothing worse</i>
<i>than having a little brother</i>

02:53.440 --> 02:54.774
<i>that's bigger than you.</i>

02:54.808 --> 02:56.643
<i>My sister, Tanya,</i>
<i>was the youngest</i>

02:56.676 --> 02:59.979
<i>and would do anything</i>
<i>to get me in trouble.</i>

03:00.013 --> 03:01.414
Chris, clean that mess up.

03:01.448 --> 03:03.283
Tanya did it.
Uh-uh!

03:03.316 --> 03:04.584
ROCHELLE:
Did I ask you that?

03:04.617 --> 03:06.286
NARRATOR:
<i>Since I was the oldest,</i>

03:06.319 --> 03:07.887
<i>I had to be</i>
<i>the emergency adult.</i>

03:07.921 --> 03:10.623
If you smell smoke, and you
think the house is gonna

03:10.657 --> 03:12.992
catch fire, get your brother
and sister and get out.

03:13.026 --> 03:16.396
If you smell gas and you think
the house is gonna blow up,

03:16.429 --> 03:18.431
get your brother and sister
and get out.

03:18.465 --> 03:21.401
If you smell smoke and your
brother catches on fire,

03:21.434 --> 03:23.269
get your sister
and get out of here.

03:23.303 --> 03:25.638
NARRATOR:
<i>Fortunately,</i>
<i>the house never caught fire</i>

03:25.672 --> 03:27.040
<i>and neither did my brother.</i>

03:27.073 --> 03:28.675
Mom, why is it
that Drew and Tanya

03:28.708 --> 03:30.777
get to go to school
in our own neighborhood,

03:30.810 --> 03:32.979
but I have to go all
the way to Brooklyn Beach?

03:33.013 --> 03:35.982
NARRATOR:
<i>Brooklyn Beach was</i>
<i>a poor Italian neighborhood</i>

03:36.016 --> 03:37.384
<i>on the other side of town.</i>

03:37.417 --> 03:38.718
<i>It was just like Bed-Stuy:</i>

03:38.752 --> 03:40.720
<i>take away the gangs,</i>
<i>add the mob.</i>

03:40.754 --> 03:43.490
Because the junior
high school around here

03:43.523 --> 03:45.792
is like a hoodlum factory.

03:45.825 --> 03:48.595
Now, those white kids,
they get an education.

03:48.628 --> 03:50.530
NARRATOR:
<i>Not a Harvard-type education,</i>

03:50.563 --> 03:53.566
<i>just a not-sticking-up-</i>
<i>a-liquor-store type education.</i>

03:53.600 --> 03:55.735
Hey, Dad.
Hi, baby.

03:55.769 --> 03:58.304
What's up?
Oh, what's up, Dad?

03:58.338 --> 04:00.607
Hey, Daddy.
Hey, baby.

04:00.640 --> 04:02.642
NARRATOR:
<i>Tanya was</i>
<i>my father's favorite.</i>

04:02.676 --> 04:04.411
What's wrong with
your oatmeal?

04:04.444 --> 04:05.612
Chris made
it too lumpy.

04:05.645 --> 04:07.347
NARRATOR:
<i>And she knew it.</i>

04:07.380 --> 04:09.716
You don't
have to eat it.

04:12.585 --> 04:15.655
JULIUS:
I know you're not
gonna throw that away.

04:15.689 --> 04:16.690
Eat that.

04:16.723 --> 04:18.758
That's 30 cent
worth of oatmeal.

04:18.792 --> 04:21.895
NARRATOR:
<i>My father always knew</i>
<i>what everything cost.</i>

04:21.928 --> 04:24.931
That's a $1.09 in the trash!

04:24.964 --> 04:28.935
That's two dollars on fire.

04:28.968 --> 04:31.871
That's 49 cent of spilt milk

04:31.905 --> 04:33.573
dripping all over my table.

04:33.606 --> 04:35.975
Somebody gonna drink this milk.

04:36.009 --> 04:37.944
Uh, baby,
did you see this?

04:37.977 --> 04:40.480
Mm. Oh, I paid this.

04:40.513 --> 04:42.582
It says you paid half.
I know.

04:42.615 --> 04:44.050
I gave you all the money.

04:44.084 --> 04:45.819
How come you only paid
half the bill?

04:45.852 --> 04:48.521
I cannot even believe that
you're asking me that.

04:48.555 --> 04:49.789
I'm asking you
a question.

04:49.823 --> 04:51.791
I'm trying to find out
what's going on--

04:51.825 --> 04:54.060
No, you're not.
You're questioning my judgment.

04:54.094 --> 04:57.397
You act like there's not a big
red bill sitting on the table.

04:57.430 --> 04:59.899
Okay, fine.
You do it, then.

04:59.933 --> 05:03.436
I will. I am. Fine.
Okay. Good. Fine.

05:03.470 --> 05:06.539
NARRATOR:
<i>My parents taught me love</i>
<i>is never having to say:</i>

05:06.573 --> 05:09.009
<i>"Kiss my ass!"</i>
Where the stamps at?

05:09.042 --> 05:11.144
NARRATOR:
<i>I was never cool growing up.</i>

05:11.177 --> 05:12.679
<i>The coolest thing about me</i>

05:12.712 --> 05:14.948
<i>was this pair</i>
<i>of white sneakers I had.</i>

05:14.981 --> 05:16.549
Oh, no, no, no.

05:16.583 --> 05:18.651
You are not going to school
in those sneakers.

05:18.685 --> 05:20.754
NARRATOR:
<i>Believe it or not,</i>
<i>there was a time</i>

05:20.787 --> 05:22.822
<i>when you couldn't wear sneakers</i>
<i>everywhere.</i>

05:22.856 --> 05:24.691
Why? Everybody else
wears sneakers.

05:24.724 --> 05:25.959
Because you look raggedy.

05:25.992 --> 05:27.994
And plus,
you have an assembly today.

05:28.028 --> 05:29.562
Boy, you done lost your mind.

05:29.596 --> 05:31.097
NARRATOR:
<i>My mother hated raggedy.</i>

05:31.131 --> 05:33.633
<i>She always said it's better</i>
<i>to be poor and neat</i>

05:33.667 --> 05:35.101
<i>than rich and raggedy.</i>

05:35.135 --> 05:37.804
<i>I think she said that</i>
<i>because we were poor.</i>

05:37.837 --> 05:41.408
Here.
Wear Drew's good shoes.

05:41.441 --> 05:42.809
I hate these shoes.

05:42.842 --> 05:44.778
Everybody will make fun
of me at school.

05:44.811 --> 05:46.646
You've been going there
for a week.

05:46.680 --> 05:48.448
You don't know everybody.

05:48.481 --> 05:51.017
NARRATOR:
<i>I was the only black kid</i>
<i>at the school.</i>

05:51.051 --> 05:52.152
They know me.

05:53.486 --> 05:54.888
NARRATOR:
<i>This is so embarrassing.</i>

05:54.921 --> 05:56.623
How come he's
wearing my shoes?

05:56.656 --> 05:58.558
'Cause you only have
one pair of feet.

05:58.591 --> 06:00.126
Chris, don't fool around
after school.

06:00.160 --> 06:02.862
I need you to be here
to let Drew and Tanya in, okay?

06:02.896 --> 06:04.998
You won't be here?
I got to work today.

06:05.031 --> 06:06.132
But you know the drill.

06:06.166 --> 06:07.767
Yeah, yeah,
I know, I know.

06:07.801 --> 06:10.470
Daddy's gonna be asleep,
don't wake him up till 5:00.

06:10.503 --> 06:13.006
That's right. Chris.

06:13.039 --> 06:14.774
You got your bus pass?

06:14.808 --> 06:16.676
Yeah. Um...

06:16.710 --> 06:18.878
somewhere around here.
Mm-hmm.

06:18.912 --> 06:20.780
You keep on.
You lose this bus pass,

06:20.814 --> 06:23.216
and your behind is gonna be
walking to school.

06:23.249 --> 06:25.752
Oh.

06:25.785 --> 06:27.787
Here's two dollars for lunch.
Thanks.

06:27.821 --> 06:29.723
All right.
Now, be good.

06:29.756 --> 06:31.458
CHRIS: I will.
Bye, Mommy.

06:31.491 --> 06:32.892
Bye, baby.

06:32.926 --> 06:34.160
Hold your sister's hand.

06:34.194 --> 06:36.863
Don't go in the street.

06:38.998 --> 06:41.601
NARRATOR:
<i>Keisha was the girl next door.</i>

06:41.634 --> 06:43.903
<i>At 13, I didn't know</i>
<i>a lot about sex,</i>

06:43.937 --> 06:46.172
<i>but I knew she had something</i>
<i>to do with it.</i>

06:46.206 --> 06:48.041
Hey, Drew.
NARRATOR:<i>Drew?!</i>

06:48.074 --> 06:49.542
What's up, Keisha?

06:51.945 --> 06:53.646
You know her?

06:53.680 --> 06:55.115
Yeah.

06:55.148 --> 06:57.584
NARRATOR:
<i>Drew was so cool,</i>
<i>he got girls at 10</i>

06:57.617 --> 06:59.619
<i>that I couldn't get</i>
<i>until I was 30.</i>

06:59.652 --> 07:01.121
Listen, when y'all
get to the house,

07:01.154 --> 07:03.623
don't ring the bell
or knock on the door.

07:03.656 --> 07:05.892
Just wait, okay?
Whatever.

07:05.925 --> 07:07.794
What if I have to go
to the bathroom?

07:07.827 --> 07:10.163
Go at school.
That bathroom is so nasty.

07:10.196 --> 07:12.866
Listen,
if you wake up Daddy,

07:12.899 --> 07:15.068
he's gonna punch me
square in the face.

07:15.101 --> 07:17.871
And if he does that,
I'm gonna punch you in the face.

07:17.904 --> 07:20.607
And then he's gonna kill me
and wind up in jail.

07:20.640 --> 07:22.509
Now, do you want Daddy
to go to jail?

07:22.542 --> 07:24.210
No.
[MOCKINGLY] No?

07:24.244 --> 07:26.546
[NORMALLY]
All right, then!

07:26.579 --> 07:28.548
NARRATOR:
<i>Even when my mother got mad,</i>

07:28.581 --> 07:30.250
<i>she still made</i>
<i>my dad's dinner.</i>

07:30.283 --> 07:31.818
...have this on my mind.

07:31.851 --> 07:33.620
NARRATOR:
<i>...vegetables, potatoes,</i>

07:33.653 --> 07:36.823
<i>and his favorite:</i>
<i>a big piece of chicken.</i>

07:36.856 --> 07:39.893
<i>I had to take two buses</i>
<i>to school every day.</i>

07:39.926 --> 07:42.162
<i>Was the junior high school</i>
<i>across the street</i>

07:42.195 --> 07:43.563
<i>really that bad?</i>

07:43.596 --> 07:46.299
[GUNSHOTS]
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

07:46.332 --> 07:47.967
NARRATOR:
<i>Much like rock and roll,</i>

07:48.001 --> 07:50.603
<i>school shootings were also</i>
<i>invented by blacks</i>

07:50.637 --> 07:53.606
<i>and stolen by the white man.</i>

07:53.640 --> 07:56.676
<i>My first bus</i>
<i>was the 26.</i>

07:56.710 --> 07:59.012
<i>I read the newspaper</i>
<i>every single day.</i>

07:59.045 --> 08:00.880
<i>I learned more</i>
<i>on the way to school</i>

08:00.914 --> 08:03.516
<i>than I learned at school.</i>

08:04.918 --> 08:07.120
<i>My next bus was the 44.</i>

08:07.153 --> 08:09.556
<i>I was the only black person</i>
<i>on the bus.</i>

08:09.589 --> 08:11.324
<i>And nobody would sit</i>
<i>next to me.</i>

08:11.358 --> 08:13.026
<i>I mean, nobody.</i>

08:13.993 --> 08:15.729
<i>If you think she's mad now,</i>

08:15.762 --> 08:17.831
<i>wait till her daughter</i>
<i>brings home O.J.</i>

08:17.864 --> 08:19.966
[STUDENTS CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

08:20.000 --> 08:22.602
NARRATOR:
<i>My mother thought</i>
<i>going to a white school</i>

08:22.635 --> 08:24.304
<i>meant I would get</i>
<i>a better education</i>

08:24.337 --> 08:26.239
<i>and I would be safer.</i>

08:26.272 --> 08:28.241
<i>Wrong!</i>

08:28.274 --> 08:30.010
<i>That's Joey Caruso,</i>

08:30.043 --> 08:32.579
<i>a little thug with a big chip</i>
<i>on his shoulder.</i>

08:32.612 --> 08:34.147
<i>You know,</i>
<i>I managed to avoid him</i>

08:34.180 --> 08:36.049
<i>before I wore these shoes.</i>

08:37.117 --> 08:38.651
Nice shoes, Bojangles.

08:38.685 --> 08:40.854
Bojangles?

08:40.887 --> 08:42.756
That's not what
your mother called me

08:42.789 --> 08:45.258
when I was tap-dancing
in her drawers last night.

08:45.291 --> 08:47.360
[STUDENTS GASP, EXCLAIM]

08:47.394 --> 08:50.130
NARRATOR:
<i>I know you think I'm crazy,</i>
<i>but if I let him</i>

08:50.163 --> 08:53.166
<i>get away with that,</i>
<i>he'd be doing it all year.</i>

08:53.199 --> 08:54.768
<i>Now, I couldn't beat him,</i>

08:54.801 --> 08:57.137
<i>but I thought maybe</i>
<i>I could out-black him.</i>

08:57.170 --> 08:59.172
What?
Did I stutter?

08:59.205 --> 09:01.908
[STUDENTS EXCLAIM]
Do you know who I am?

09:01.941 --> 09:03.643
You step on
my shoe again,

09:03.677 --> 09:04.911
and I'mma tell you
who I am.

09:04.944 --> 09:06.880
[STUDENTS EXCLAIM]
I don't play that.

09:06.913 --> 09:08.615
I'm from Bed-Stuy, boy.

09:08.648 --> 09:10.917
I'll bring half of
Marcy up in here.

09:10.950 --> 09:12.686
I will beat
your butt so bad,

09:12.719 --> 09:14.688
you're gonna need
crutches in your sleep.

09:14.721 --> 09:16.022
NARRATOR:
<i>Hey, this might work.</i>

09:16.056 --> 09:17.957
You know what else
I'm gonna do--

09:17.991 --> 09:19.025
[CROWD GASPS]

09:19.059 --> 09:21.127
What's your name?
Chris.

09:21.161 --> 09:23.763
I'm Dr. Raymond,
your new principal.

09:23.797 --> 09:26.066
Now get off my feet.

09:26.099 --> 09:29.069
[SNICKERING]
RAYMOND: That's funny?

09:29.102 --> 09:30.370
That's not funny.

09:30.403 --> 09:32.272
What's your name, son?

09:32.305 --> 09:33.840
Caruso.

09:33.873 --> 09:36.376
Fix yourself up
next time you come to my school.

09:38.445 --> 09:40.146
See those shoes?

09:40.180 --> 09:41.948
They say something.

09:41.981 --> 09:43.350
They say, "I'm a student.

09:43.383 --> 09:45.719
I want to learn."

09:45.752 --> 09:47.821
I want more of that...

09:47.854 --> 09:50.056
and less of this.

09:50.090 --> 09:51.691
[***]

09:52.692 --> 09:54.427
Don't bump into me again.

09:54.461 --> 09:57.263
NARRATOR:
<i>Even though Caruso</i>
<i>was messing with</i>me,

09:57.297 --> 09:59.966
<i>getting embarrassed</i>
<i>made him even madder.</i>

10:00.000 --> 10:01.768
<i>So you know what's coming next.</i>

10:01.801 --> 10:03.103
This isn't over, nigger.

10:04.437 --> 10:07.107
NARRATOR:
<i>Oh, he got away with calling me</i>
<i>nigger that day.</i>

10:07.140 --> 10:09.976
<i>But later in life,</i>
<i>he said it at a DMX concert</i>

10:10.010 --> 10:12.746
<i>and almost got stomped</i>
<i>to death.</i>

10:12.779 --> 10:15.782
Hey, are you really from
Bed-Stuy, do or die?

10:15.815 --> 10:17.984
Yeah.
You ever been shot?

10:18.018 --> 10:21.287
No.
Well, at least not yet.

10:21.321 --> 10:23.323
I'm Greg.
I'm Chris.

10:23.356 --> 10:25.792
NARRATOR:
<i>Greg Wuliger</i>
<i>wasn't my first choice</i>

10:25.825 --> 10:27.827
<i>for a friend,</i>
<i>but mutual ass-kicking</i>

10:27.861 --> 10:29.362
<i>seemed to bring</i>
<i>people together.</i>

10:29.396 --> 10:31.965
Cool shoes.
Thanks.

10:31.998 --> 10:34.300
You know, if that
was the new principal,

10:34.334 --> 10:35.869
who was the old one?

10:35.902 --> 10:37.370
I didn't touch her!

10:37.404 --> 10:40.040
I don't know what you're
talking about. Ask anybody.

10:40.073 --> 10:41.941
NARRATOR:
<i>Mr. Palmer was accused</i>
<i>of doing something</i>

10:41.975 --> 10:44.377
<i>we can't tell you about</i>
<i>because of the network censors.</i>

10:44.411 --> 10:46.146
<i>The school settled</i>
<i>the lawsuit out of court,</i>

10:46.179 --> 10:48.048
<i>and he's not allowed</i>
<i>to teach anymore.</i>

10:48.081 --> 10:49.816
<i>If he moves to your</i>
<i>neighborhood,</i>

10:49.849 --> 10:52.018
<i>you'll get a warning.</i>

10:52.052 --> 10:54.254
<i>Back at home, my father</i>
<i>should have been in bed,</i>

10:54.287 --> 10:56.890
<i>but he'd rather</i>
<i>lose sleep than money.</i>

10:56.923 --> 10:58.425
What are you doing?

10:58.458 --> 11:00.060
I'm paying the bills.

11:00.093 --> 11:03.129
See? It says $40,
I'm paying $40.

11:03.163 --> 11:06.766
And that's exactly why I don't
let you pay the bills.

11:06.800 --> 11:08.902
[***]

11:10.470 --> 11:12.372
Where are you going?
To work.

11:12.405 --> 11:14.941
Is Chris gonna be home
in time to wake me up?

11:14.974 --> 11:16.343
Can I see in the future?

11:16.376 --> 11:17.911
What's wrong with you?

11:19.913 --> 11:23.016
[DOOR CLOSES]
Probably can see in the future.

11:25.952 --> 11:27.887
NARRATOR:
<i>By lunchtime, I was starving.</i>

11:27.921 --> 11:29.422
GREG:
I'm gonna go
get a hot dog.

11:29.456 --> 11:31.991
I'm gonna get
a slice of pizza.

11:34.160 --> 11:35.095
Got my money...

11:36.229 --> 11:38.231
[***]

11:41.401 --> 11:43.003
Give me back my bus pass.

11:43.036 --> 11:45.772
You want it?
Take it, you little...

11:49.943 --> 11:52.912
After school, Satchmo.

12:05.358 --> 12:07.460
NARRATOR:
<i>After school, I had a plan.</i>

12:07.494 --> 12:09.195
Th-This is crazy.

12:09.229 --> 12:12.065
Man, it's a school fight. School
fights only last a minute,

12:12.098 --> 12:14.334
'cause somebody always
comes and breaks them up.

12:14.367 --> 12:16.803
All I have to do is get
in the first punch,

12:16.836 --> 12:18.905
somebody'll stop it.

12:18.938 --> 12:20.907
CROWD [CHANTING]:
<i>Fight! Fight! Fight!</i>

12:20.940 --> 12:23.109
[CHANTING CONTINUES]

12:24.310 --> 12:26.946
What're you waiting
for, Corn Bread?

12:27.947 --> 12:29.582
[CROWD EXCLAIMS]

12:29.616 --> 12:31.484
This'll be over any minute.

12:31.518 --> 12:33.820
[***]

12:39.325 --> 12:41.528
[***]

12:54.174 --> 12:57.043
Is somebody
gonna stop this?

13:01.481 --> 13:03.083
[GROANS]

13:09.889 --> 13:12.959
Wait! Wait! Wait!

13:12.992 --> 13:14.094
Wait for me!

13:14.127 --> 13:16.496
Thank you. Thank you, yeah.

13:16.529 --> 13:18.598
Come on, ma'am, come on.
I got a schedule. Let's go...

13:18.631 --> 13:21.134
Wait! Wait! Hold up!
Hold up! Wait!

13:21.167 --> 13:22.869
There's a kid
trying to catch...

13:22.902 --> 13:25.138
Yeah, yeah, I know, I see...

13:25.171 --> 13:26.973
Wait, wait,
wait, wait-- Ow!

13:27.007 --> 13:28.875
[GRUMBLING]

13:31.011 --> 13:32.512
Bet you don't get me tomorrow.

13:32.545 --> 13:33.880
I bet I do.

13:33.913 --> 13:35.215
You do...
Yeah, go sit down.

13:35.248 --> 13:37.584
Cut that out, you bunch
of hoods! Back off!

13:41.021 --> 13:44.024
NARRATOR:
<i>I was still hungry,</i>
<i>but I was almost home.</i>

13:44.057 --> 13:45.558
<i>What could go wrong now?</i>

13:45.592 --> 13:47.360
Daddy!

13:47.394 --> 13:50.296
Daddy! Daddy!

13:50.330 --> 13:52.599
NARRATOR:
<i>That girl's trying</i>
<i>to get me killed.</i>

13:52.632 --> 13:54.668
Daddy! Dad--

13:54.701 --> 13:56.670
Girl, you don't want
Daddy to go to jail.

13:56.703 --> 13:58.371
I told her to quit.

13:58.405 --> 14:01.374
I have to go to the bathroom.
I told you to go at school!

14:01.408 --> 14:03.910
That bathroom is nasty!

14:06.079 --> 14:08.081
Listen. We're going in.

14:08.114 --> 14:10.583
But once we get in, I don't
want to hear any noise.

14:10.617 --> 14:12.452
None.
Do you understand?

14:12.485 --> 14:13.420
Yes.

14:14.954 --> 14:17.457
[***]

14:17.490 --> 14:19.426
[TOILET FLUSHING]

14:22.495 --> 14:25.465
[CONTINUES FLUSHING, MUFFLED]

14:25.498 --> 14:28.268
NARRATOR:
<i>My father always</i>
<i>slept in his uniform.</i>

14:28.301 --> 14:32.072
<i>That way, when he woke up,</i>
<i>he'd be ready to go.</i>

14:33.073 --> 14:34.607
[FLOORBOARDS CREAK]

14:34.641 --> 14:36.076
I know how
to pay bills.

14:36.109 --> 14:37.344
I can pay the bills...

14:48.488 --> 14:50.423
[LATCH CLICKS]

14:50.457 --> 14:53.293
NARRATOR:
<i>You may not think messing up</i>
<i>a pair of $40 shoes</i>

14:53.326 --> 14:56.196
<i>is such a big deal,</i>
<i>but you have to realize</i>

14:56.229 --> 14:58.665
<i>that my father's car</i>
<i>only cost $65.</i>

14:58.698 --> 15:00.433
<i>I had to get those shoes clean.</i>

15:00.467 --> 15:02.402
[***]

15:27.694 --> 15:31.297
NARRATOR:
<i>For the first time that day,</i>
<i>things were going all right.</i>

15:36.336 --> 15:40.240
<i>All I had to do now was keep</i>
<i>everybody quiet till 5:00.</i>

15:40.273 --> 15:41.641
[LAUGHING]

15:41.675 --> 15:43.677
[MUFFLED LAUGHING]

15:43.710 --> 15:46.012
[CLOCK TICKING]

15:50.717 --> 15:52.185
Dad...

15:52.218 --> 15:53.987
Dad.

15:54.454 --> 15:56.222
Time to get up.

15:57.090 --> 15:58.525
It's 5:00?

15:58.558 --> 16:00.560
Yep.

16:00.593 --> 16:03.263
It's not 4:59?

16:03.296 --> 16:04.798
Nope.

16:04.831 --> 16:06.766
No...

16:07.734 --> 16:09.302
What job am I
going to?

16:09.336 --> 16:11.571
You're driving a truck.

16:11.604 --> 16:13.340
[SIGHS]

16:16.776 --> 16:19.212
[GROANS]

16:19.245 --> 16:21.748
[PHONE RINGS]
Hello?

16:21.781 --> 16:23.683
Hey, hey, baby.
It's Mommy.

16:23.717 --> 16:24.818
Is your father up?

16:24.851 --> 16:26.419
Yep.
<i>Good, good, good.</i>

16:26.453 --> 16:28.555
Take his plate
out of the refrigerator

16:28.588 --> 16:29.823
and put in the oven for him.

16:29.856 --> 16:31.324
What plate?

16:31.358 --> 16:33.560
The one with
the big piece of chicken.

16:33.593 --> 16:35.528
[***]

16:46.539 --> 16:48.108
Haven't I told you

16:48.141 --> 16:51.244
do not eat
the big piece of chicken?

16:51.277 --> 16:52.812
But I was still hungry.

16:52.846 --> 16:55.215
NARRATOR:
<i>My mother wasn't mad at me,</i>
<i>she was</i>

16:55.248 --> 16:57.484
<i>looking out for my father.</i>
You see how big he is?

16:57.517 --> 16:59.786
NARRATOR:
<i>She didn't want him</i>
<i>to go to work hungry,</i>

16:59.819 --> 17:02.489
<i>'cause if he goes to work</i>
<i>hungry, he'll be grouchy,</i>

17:02.522 --> 17:05.258
<i>and if he's grouchy, he might</i>
<i>call his boss "cracker,"</i>

17:05.291 --> 17:06.726
<i>and if he calls</i>
<i>his boss "cracker,"</i>

17:06.760 --> 17:08.862
<i>then we're living</i>
<i>in the projects again.</i>

17:08.895 --> 17:13.366
But do not eat the biggest
piece of chicken.

17:14.200 --> 17:16.436
Do you understand?

17:21.574 --> 17:24.210
At least you didn't
mess up your school shoes.

17:28.481 --> 17:30.684
Now come over here
and give me some sugar.

17:30.717 --> 17:32.819
[***]

17:35.822 --> 17:37.590
Now go to bed.

17:41.161 --> 17:42.529
Rochelle.

17:42.562 --> 17:43.763
What?

17:43.797 --> 17:45.799
Look, I'm not trying
to tell you what to do,

17:45.832 --> 17:48.468
but I'm working hard trying
to pay for this place.

17:48.501 --> 17:50.537
You know that.
Just because you make money

17:50.570 --> 17:52.439
doesn't mean you know
how to spend it.

17:52.472 --> 17:54.541
You got to know how
to work the system.

17:54.574 --> 17:55.608
What system?

17:55.642 --> 17:57.377
The debt system.

17:57.410 --> 18:00.480
I run this house like they run
the country: on a deficit.

18:00.513 --> 18:03.149
Rent is due on the 3rd.
I don't pay it till the 9th

18:03.183 --> 18:05.352
because you don't get
your check till the 7th.

18:05.385 --> 18:07.220
If you pay
the light bill now,

18:07.253 --> 18:08.722
I won't have money
for the groceries,

18:08.755 --> 18:10.824
the rent would be late and then
you'll have to work overtime.

18:10.857 --> 18:12.592
You want to work
overtime again?

18:12.625 --> 18:13.660
No, I don't think so.

18:13.693 --> 18:15.362
If we don't owe people money,

18:15.395 --> 18:17.330
we won't have any money at all.

18:18.865 --> 18:21.601
[SIGHS]
Um...

18:21.634 --> 18:24.371
Uh, why didn't you
just say that then?

18:24.404 --> 18:26.539
Because you didn't ask.

18:30.744 --> 18:32.178
Baby.

18:32.212 --> 18:34.280
Don't "baby" me.

18:34.314 --> 18:37.384
Come here. I'm sorry.

18:37.417 --> 18:38.885
Okay?

18:40.487 --> 18:42.655
Who told you to open
the mail, anyway?

18:42.689 --> 18:45.291
Come here, pookie.

18:45.325 --> 18:47.527
No, last time you said
"pookie," I got pregnant.

18:47.560 --> 18:49.462
You my pookie.
You always my pookie.

18:49.496 --> 18:52.565
No pookie.
Okay, little bit of pookie.

18:52.599 --> 18:54.200
Love you.

18:54.234 --> 18:55.902
I love you too, baby.

18:58.705 --> 19:01.441
NARRATOR:
<i>My dad always checked on us</i>
<i>in between jobs,</i>

19:01.474 --> 19:04.644
<i>his night job</i>
<i>and his late-at-night job.</i>

19:04.678 --> 19:05.979
Dad?

19:06.012 --> 19:08.214
Hey, man.

19:08.248 --> 19:10.417
I thought you were asleep.

19:10.450 --> 19:12.852
I'm sorry I ate
the big piece of chicken.

19:12.886 --> 19:14.888
That was 89 cent
worth of chicken.

19:14.921 --> 19:17.424
What, you didn't get enough
to eat at school?

19:17.457 --> 19:19.259
I was still hungry.

19:19.292 --> 19:21.361
Now I'm still hungry.

19:21.394 --> 19:22.729
Look, next time,

19:22.762 --> 19:25.432
eat a little something
extra at breakfast, okay?

19:25.465 --> 19:26.433
Okay.

19:26.933 --> 19:28.902
Here.

19:28.935 --> 19:30.904
Now don't go pulling
this money out.

19:30.937 --> 19:33.373
Somebody'll try to rob you.

19:33.406 --> 19:35.608
Don't tell
your mother about this.

19:35.642 --> 19:37.377
[***]

19:37.410 --> 19:38.945
Everything okay at school?

19:38.978 --> 19:40.947
NARRATOR:
<i>I didn't tell him</i>
<i>about the fight.</i>

19:40.980 --> 19:43.950
<i>My dad went to school</i>
<i>during the Civil Rights era.</i>

19:43.983 --> 19:48.021
<i>After hoses, tanks and</i>
<i>the dog bites on your ass,</i>

19:48.054 --> 19:50.290
<i>somehow Joey Caruso</i>
<i>didn't compare.</i>

19:50.323 --> 19:53.360
Yeah, it was all right.

19:54.694 --> 19:57.263
Good. I'll see you
in the morning.

19:57.297 --> 20:00.266
NARRATOR:
<i>My father wasn't the type</i>
<i>to say, "I love you."</i>

20:00.300 --> 20:02.736
<i>He was one of four fathers</i>
<i>on the block.</i>

20:02.769 --> 20:05.672
<i>"I'll see you in the morning,"</i>
<i>meant he was coming home.</i>

20:05.705 --> 20:09.042
<i>Coming home was his way</i>
<i>of saying, "I love you."</i>

20:09.075 --> 20:10.643
Unplug that clock, boy.

20:10.677 --> 20:12.846
You can't tell time
when you sleep.

20:12.879 --> 20:14.681
That's two cents an hour.

20:15.982 --> 20:18.718
ROCHELLE:
What the hell happened
to my towel?

20:18.752 --> 20:20.720
[***]

20:31.698 --> 20:33.633
[***]

20:34.934 --> 20:38.405
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>
